                <note type="abstract">Examination of Theodore's tract "On Icon Veneration". The author argues that his use of biblical quotations, brought in Arabic, is a form of intertextuality in that it seeks to establish a correspondence between the Bible and the Qurʾān. Muslim allegations are thus rejected, while Christians are encouraged to hold to their traditions. Quoting Gen 1:31; 2:18; 2:10-14; 2:21-22; 3:1; 3:8; 6:6; 8:21; 11:7; 18; 18:11-12; 18:20-21; 19:26; 21:2; 23:7; 27:29; 28:13; 33:3; 42:6; 47:3; 48:12; 49:8; Exod 3:2; 4:3; 12:46; 14:21; 15:25-26; 17:6; 18:7; 20:2-5; (20:4; 20:4-5; 20:5); 24:18; 25:8-9; 25:18; 25:20; 25:22; 25:40; 28:9-12; 28:15-17; 28:21; 28:29-30; 31:12-13; 31:16-17; 32:11-14; 33:7-10; 40:34; Lev 9:24; 17:7; 17:8-9; Num 20:11; 21:8; 21:8-9; 21:9; 22:28; Deut 4:24; 5:8-9; 6:13; 9:25; 23:12-15; Josh 4:4-9; 7:6; 10:12-13; 1 Sam 21:5-7; 2 Sam 6:14; 1 Kgs 1:16; 1:23; 1:31; 1:53; 2:19; 7:19, 23, 25, 29, 36; 8:10-11; 17:1; 18:1, 41-46; 18:30-35; 19:8; 2 Kgs 2:15; 5:13-14; 6:6; 13:21; 18:4; 1 Chr 28:11-19; 29:20; 2 Chr 3:10, 13; 7:1; Isa 6:5; 19:1; 41:8; 49:14-17; 56:11; 58:13; 66:1; Jer 51:59-64; Ezek 1:10, 15; 1:26; 1:28; 4:1-3; 8:2; 16; 20:21; 20:25; 41:15-20; Dan 3:24-25; 6:10; 7:9; 10:2; 10:4; 12:4; 12:6; Hos 2; 12:10; Jonah 1:7; 2:10; Ps 5:8; 28:2; 72:11; 96:5; 99:5; 132:6; 132:7; 132:8; 132:14; 1 Macc 2:41; 2 Macc 6:18-7:41; Prov 19:17.</note>
            </biblStruct>
